					<img class="f-img img-fluid mx-auto" src="img/blog_1.jpg" alt="">
					<h4>
						<a href="#">HOME HEALTH VS IN-HOME CARE</a>
					</h4>
					<p style="text-align:justify">
						In short, home health is an extension of medical care and private care is additional in-home support for people
						who have difficulty performing everyday tasks.

						Home health is usually for an allotted period of time and takes the form of rehabilitation similar to what one
						might experience in a skilled nursing or outpatient rehab facility. This must be ordered by a doctor and is
						typically covered (at least in part) through medical insurance.
					</p>
